  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "We can see on line 6 of the contract code https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/deposit_contract/contracts/validator_registration.vy#L6\r\n\r\nwithdrawal_credentials is only taking 32 bytes. Same thing inside an event definition but inside `deposit` function arguments we see a dynamic `bytes` array. https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/deposit_contract/contracts/validator_registration.vy#L68\r\nIs this deliberate? Couldn't we use `bytes32` type there instead of dynamic `bytes` array? ",
